TI  - Deep Learning Models for Real-Time Object Recognition: Transforming Autonomous Vehicle Safety and Navigation Capabilities
AU  - Sharanya, C.
AU  - Karthikeya, K.V.
AU  - Antony Saviour, Mariya Princy
AU  - Gomathi, P.S.
AU  - Pandi, V. Samuthira
AU  - Prakalya, S.B.
AB  - Real-time object recognition has been transformed by deep learning models, which have contributed to revolutionary increases in the capabilities of autonomous cars in terms of both safety and navigation. Object identification and classification systems are able to process enormous volumes of sensor data with an unparalleled level of speed and accuracy. This is made possible by the utilization of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and advanced neural architectures. The potential of deep learning to recognize objects, pedestrians, road signs, and barriers in dynamic situations is highlighted in this research, which investigates the vital role that deep learning plays in autonomous vehicle systems. Several important difficulties, such as the optimization of the model, the efficiency of the computation, and the robustness in a variety of lighting and environments, are addressed. When it comes to enhancing vehicle decision-making, collision avoidance, and overall navigation performance, we also examine the impact that these models have on these areas. We demonstrate, by means of our research, that real-time deep learning-based object recognition is essential to the advancement of the dependability and safety of autonomous cars, hence paving the way for transportation systems that are both more secure and energy efficient.
